1. INTRODUCTION
================================================================================

In today's highly competitive business environment, effectively managing leads is
crucial for the growth and sustainability of any organization. A Lead Management
System (LMS) is a software application designed to capture, track, organize, and
nurture potential customers — called leads — through the sales pipeline from first
contact to conversion.

Traditional methods of managing leads using spreadsheets, paper records, or disparate
tools are error-prone, time-consuming, and lack real-time visibility. A centralized,
database-driven Lead Management System addresses these challenges by automating the
tracking and follow-up process, assigning leads to appropriate sales agents, and
generating meaningful analytics to improve decision-making.

This project implements a fully functional Lead Management System using:
  - Python Flask as the web application server (front-end presentation layer)
  - HTML, CSS, and JavaScript as the client-side UI
  - SQLite (default) or MySQL as the relational database back-end

The system provides role-based access simulation for Administrators, Sales Managers,
and Sales Representatives, enabling efficient collaboration and complete lead lifecycle
management with database triggers, stored procedures, and audit trails.


