7. NORMALIZATION
================================================================================

The database schema is designed to satisfy Third Normal Form (3NF) and BCNF.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
7.1 FIRST NORMAL FORM (1NF)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Requirement: All attributes must contain atomic (indivisible) values; no repeating
groups or multi-valued attributes.

Satisfaction:
  - All columns store single atomic values (e.g., first_name and last_name are
    separate columns, not a combined "full_name" array).
  - No repeating groups (e.g., multiple phone numbers are not stored in one cell).
  - Each table has a defined primary key.
  ✓ Schema is in 1NF.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
7.2 SECOND NORMAL FORM (2NF)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Requirement: Must be in 1NF AND no partial dependency on a composite primary key.

Satisfaction:
  - All tables use a single-column surrogate primary key (dept_id, rep_id, lead_id,
    customer_id, followup_id, log_id).
  - Since there are no composite primary keys, partial dependencies cannot exist.
  ✓ Schema is in 2NF.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
7.3 THIRD NORMAL FORM (3NF)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Requirement: Must be in 2NF AND no transitive dependency (non-key attribute
depending on another non-key attribute).

Analysis per table:

  departments:
    - dept_name, dept_head, location depend only on dept_id (PK).
    ✓ No transitive dependencies.

  sales_representatives:
    - name, email, phone, designation depend on rep_id (PK).
    - dept_id is a foreign key referencing departments — department details
      (dept_name, dept_head, location) are NOT duplicated here.
    ✓ No transitive dependencies.

  leads:
    - Lead attributes depend on lead_id (PK).
    - assigned_to is FK to sales_representatives — rep details are not stored
      redundantly in the leads table.
    ✓ No transitive dependencies.

  customers:
    - company_name, address, conversion_date, total_value depend on customer_id.
    - lead_id is FK — lead personal details are not duplicated.
    ✓ No transitive dependencies.

  follow_ups:
    - All attributes depend on followup_id (PK).
    - lead_id and rep_id are foreign keys only.
    ✓ No transitive dependencies.

  activity_log:
    - action, action_date, description depend on log_id (PK).
    - lead_id and rep_id are foreign keys only.
    ✓ No transitive dependencies.

  ✓ Schema is in 3NF.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
7.4 BOYCE-CODD NORMAL FORM (BCNF)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Requirement: For every functional dependency X → Y, X must be a superkey.

  - All functional dependencies in every table have the primary key on the
    left-hand side.
  - No anomalies from non-superkey determinants exist.
  ✓ Schema is in BCNF.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
7.5 DESIGN DECISIONS (Denormalization Avoided)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  - Department info is NOT stored in sales_representatives (only dept_id FK).
  - Representative name is NOT stored in leads (only assigned_to FK).
  - Lead personal info is NOT duplicated in customers (only lead_id FK).
  - Activity descriptions are stored in activity_log, not embedded in leads.

This eliminates update anomalies, insertion anomalies, and deletion anomalies.


