9. STORED PROCEDURE
================================================================================

Name: GetLeadSummaryByRep
Purpose: Retrieves analytics summary of leads assigned to a specific sales rep.

Parameters:
  IN repID INT — The representative ID to query

Returns:
  rep_id          — The representative ID
  total_leads     — Total number of leads assigned to this rep
  open_leads      — Count of leads with status = 'Open'
  converted_leads — Count of leads with status = 'Converted'

SQL Definition (MySQL):
  CREATE PROCEDURE GetLeadSummaryByRep(IN repID INT)
  BEGIN
      SELECT
          repID AS rep_id,
          COUNT(*) AS total_leads,
          SUM(CASE WHEN status = 'Open' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS open_leads,
          SUM(CASE WHEN status = 'Converted' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS converted_leads
      FROM leads
      WHERE assigned_to = repID;
  END;

Usage in Application:
  - MySQL: Called via cursor.callproc('GetLeadSummaryByRep', [rep_id])
  - SQLite: Equivalent SELECT query simulated in database.py (SQLite has no
    native stored procedure support)
  - API Endpoint: GET /api/analytics/rep/<rep_id>
  - UI: Dashboard "Stored Procedure Call" panel with representative dropdown


