10. DATABASE TRIGGER
================================================================================

Name: after_lead_insert
Event: AFTER INSERT ON leads
Purpose: Automatically creates an audit log entry whenever a new lead is inserted,
         ensuring complete audit trails without application-level code.

SQL Definition:
  CREATE TRIGGER after_lead_insert
  AFTER INSERT ON leads FOR EACH ROW
  BEGIN
      INSERT INTO activity_log(lead_id, rep_id, action, action_date, description)
      VALUES (NEW.lead_id, NEW.assigned_to, 'Lead Created', NOW(), 'New lead added.');
  END;

Behavior:
  - Fires automatically at the database level on every INSERT into leads
  - Uses NEW.lead_id and NEW.assigned_to to populate the log entry
  - Works in both SQLite and MySQL implementations
  - Demonstrates separation of business logic (audit) from application code


