CONNECTION FLOW (Example: Creating a New Lead):
  1. User fills "New Lead" modal form in browser
  2. JavaScript calls: POST /api/leads with JSON body
     { first_name, last_name, email, phone, source, assigned_to }
  3. Flask route add_lead() in app.py receives the request
  4. Validates required fields (first_name, last_name)
  5. Calls database.execute_query() with INSERT SQL
  6. Database trigger after_lead_insert fires → logs to activity_log
  7. Flask returns JSON: { "message": "Lead created successfully", "lead_id": N }
  8. JavaScript shows toast notification and refreshes leads table


CONFIGURATION (config.py):
