15. HOW THE SYSTEM WORKS (WORKFLOW)
================================================================================

LEAD LIFECYCLE:
  1. CAPTURE    → New lead entered via "New Lead" button (status: Open)
  2. ASSIGN     → Admin/Manager assigns lead to a sales representative
  3. CONTACT    → Rep updates status to "Contacted", schedules follow-ups
  4. FOLLOW-UP  → Rep conducts calls/meetings, marks follow-ups complete
  5. CONVERT    → Qualified lead converted to Customer with deal value
                  OR status set to "Lost" if lead does not convert

STARTUP SEQUENCE:
  1. Run: python app.py
  2. Flask initializes database via database.init_db()
  3. If tables don't exist → executes schema_sqlite.sql or schema_mysql.sql
  4. If tables are empty → loads mock/sample data
  5. Server starts on http://127.0.0.1:5000
  6. Browser loads index.html → JavaScript fetches initial data from APIs

DASHBOARD FEATURES:
  - Total Leads, Open Leads, Converted Customers, Total Revenue stat cards
  - Stored Procedure panel: select rep → shows assigned/open/converted counts
  - Workload Distribution: bar chart of leads per representative
  - Leads by Status and Leads by Source breakdowns

DATA INTEGRITY:
  - Foreign keys enforce valid references between tables
  - ON DELETE CASCADE: deleting a lead removes its customers and follow-ups
  - ON DELETE SET NULL: deleting a rep unassigns leads (doesn't delete them)
  - UNIQUE on customers.lead_id prevents double conversion
  - Trigger ensures every new lead is automatically audit-logged


